samine pathways, leading to increased oxidative stress and proteomic damage.\\\\n*   **Gut-Metabolome Axis:** The symptom of 'bloating' is highly suggestive of dysregulated gut microbial metabolites. This often involves a decrease in butyrate-producing species and an increase in metabolites that trigger visceral hypersensitivity.\\\\n\\\\n## 8.3 Systems Biology Integration\\\\nThe synergy between **Inflammation (Score 65)** and **Metabolic dysfunction (Score 70)** creates a state of **Mito-Inflammation**. The metabolic surplus drives proteomic stress (ER stress), which further impairs the metabolomic handling of glucose. To resolve the 'Root Cause', the clinical strategy must move beyond glycemic control to include proteomic stabilization and mitochondrial resuscitation.\\\"\\n}\",\"thoughtSignature\":\"\"}],\"role\":\"model\"},\"finishReason\":\"STOP\",\"index\":0}],\"usageMetadata\":{\"promptTokenCount\":362,\"candidatesTokenCount\":1048,\"totalTokenCount\":2819,\"promptTokensDetails\":[{\"modality\":\"TEXT\",\"tokenCount\":362}],\"thoughtsTokenCount\":1409,\"serviceTier\":\"standard\"},\"modelVersion\":\"gemini-3-flash-preview\",\"responseId\":\"nDAEau6oIe-64-EP4YzOwA4\"},\"usage\":{\"inputCharacters\":1019,\"inputImages\":0,\"inputVideos\":0,\"inputAudioFiles\":0,\"outputCharacters\":4640,\"outputImages\":0,\"outputVideos\":0,\"outputAudioFiles\":0,\"inputTokens\":362,\"outputTokens\":1048,\"thoughtsTokens\":1409,\"totalTokens\":2819},\"latencyMs\":14578.834407000002}","genkit:state":"success"},"displayName":"googleai/gemini-flash-latest","links":[],"instrumentationLibrary":{"name":"genkit-tracer","version":"v1"},"spanKind":"INTERNAL","sameProcessAsParentSpan":{"value":true},"status":{"code":0},"timeEvents":{"timeEvent":[]}},"ede5c5cdbe0e8f9b":{"spanId":"ede5c5cdbe0e8f9b","traceId":"f3b625bc5b300448757e59bb5e1d1ce0","parentSpanId":"a13769fa8cb35d36","startTime":1778659499066,"endTime":1778659511027.8462,"attributes":{"genkit:type":"util","genkit:name":"generate"